{"source_key":"sha256-b2107821ccc7f26bd76a1aced6244d1c","record_index":10,"record_hash":"sha256:62d6b1e8eca2f503a5363d75e6fbdf5ac65c05584a99bf3884d153265572d31b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:45:05.622Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Mostly enough for a minimal toolset, yes. For a normal same-branch handoff I’d use it like this:\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog sessions branch current --limit 5\n```\n\nPick the obvious latest/main session by timestamp, branch, title, or activity.\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog timeline <session-key> --limit 30\n```\n\nRead the turn list from end backwards until I see: user goal, decisions, files touched, tests run, blockers.\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --from end --limit 50\n```\n\nOpen the last meaningful turn or two, especially the final assistant summary and any user correction. If the timeline shows earlier important decisions, fetch those turns too.\n\nVerdict: enough for catch-up, but barely. The core shape is right: discover sessions, skim timeline, drill into records.\n\nWhat’s missing:\n\n- `sessions branch current` or default-to-current-branch behavior. Making agents spell the branch is needless friction.\n- Session summaries in `sessions` output: title, last user ask, last assistant status, changed files, test status, timestamp. Without this, agents will over-fetch timelines.\n- Timeline entries need record counts and turn metadata: user/assistant/tool, timestamp, short summary, maybe files touched. Otherwise `timeline` is just a pager into mystery meat.\n- `records` needs stable ordering and clear indices. If `--from end --limit 50` means reverse chronological, say so; if not, agents will mess this up.\n- A way to list “related but not same branch” sessions would help, but it can wait. Same branch covers the common laptop-to-laptop case.\n\nToo complex:\n\n- `--from start|end|<index>` is okay, but slightly fussy. I’d prefer `--before <index>` / `--after <index>` eventually. For v1, it’s fine.\n- Three entity filters on `sessions` are fine if branch/review/change are first-class GitButler concepts. If not, start with branch only.\n\nRedundant:\n\n- Nothing major. `timeline` and `records` are not redundant if timeline is a skim view and records is raw/detail view.\n\nOne concrete improvement I’d make: let `timeline` include the last assistant message excerpt per turn. That alone makes this usable without inventing a magic handoff command.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:45:05.622Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}